remarks.para: The Dispose method releases the resources used by the CGPath class.

Calling the Dispose method when the application is finished using the CGPath ensures that all external resources used by this managed object are released as soon as possible. Once developers have invoked the Dispose method, the object is no longer useful and developers should no longer make any calls to it.
